cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as polyphone disambiguation in Mandarin Chinese. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it mentions the front-end processing of Mandarin Chinese text-to-speech systems. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for prediction, which suggests it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of embeddings and lookup tables suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
